BARBERTON – The first day of school for the grade one class at Mountain View Primary School was without drama. Lowvelder visited the school, and both teachers and learners were ready for their first day of learning last Wednesday. Read More: Young athlete dreams of being a world champ While many of the children were very excited for their first day at school, some could not hold back the tears. Parents were seen comforting their children and teachers helped the new ones settle in. According to Hester du Toit, one of the teachers, a total of 97 learners enrolled for grade one in the 2019 academic year.